FILE: Finance Minister Tito Mboweni. GCIS JOHANNESBURG - Former Finance Minister Tito Mboweni has resigned as a Member of Parliament. READ: SACP calls for expansion of South African Reserve Bank mandate Parliament confirmed Mboweni’s resignation is effective from Monday. Mboweni, who resigned as Finance Minister in August 2021, has been an MP since 1994. National Assembly Speaker, Nosiviwe Mapisa-Nqakula, has wished Mboweni well in his retirement from Parliament. It's believed Mboweni will be joining the private sector. It has been a long journey. Sometimes very lonely! pic.twitter.com/sojkTV4TJw This is to confirm that former Minister of Finance, Mr Tito Mboweni, has handed his resignation as MP in the National Assembly to Speaker Nosiviwe Mapisa-Nqakula. The resignation is effective from today, 31 January 2022. Speaker wishes the former Minister well on his retirement. pic.twitter.com/QJmzyQMkzH